<!-- ========================================== -->
<!-- 5. CONTENT SECTION 1 -->
<!-- ========================================== -->
<h1>1 INTRODUCTION</h1>

<h2>1.1 Purpose</h2>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>This Software Requirement Specification (SRS) document defines and completely describes the functional requirements, non-functional requirements, system architecture, database structure, and communication protocols for the <b>NEXUS Parking Building Management System (PBMS)</b>. This document serves as the official technical guide for the engineering team, QA analysts, and serves as the product acceptance baseline for the Building Management Board.</p>

<h2>1.2 Scope</h2>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>The NEXUS PBMS is an automated multi-story parking management platform designed to control vehicle flows across 5 parking floors (B2, B1, G, F1, F2). The solution encompasses three core subsystems:</p>
<ul type=disc>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Web Operations Dashboard</b>: A central operator console where building management can visually monitor real-time floor maps, control EV charging station parameters, process gate exit checkout invoices, adjust tariffs, and review automated revenue charts.</li>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Driver Mobile App</b>: A mobile application compiled as a native Android APK (built with the Capacitor framework) that allows drivers to register/login, automatically request parking spot allocation, view their digital e-Ticket QR Code, and check EV charging status in real time.</li>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Express Backend Server</b>: A Node.js/Express server connecting to a PostgreSQL database, exposing RESTful APIs to synchronize real-time parking states between the Web Dashboard and the Mobile App.</li>
</ul>

<h2>1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations</h2>
<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style='border-collapse:collapse;border:solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt;'>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th width="30%">Acronym / Term</th>
      <th>Definition / Explanation</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><b>PBMS</b></td>
      <td>Parking Building Management System (Hệ thống Quản lý Tòa nhà Đỗ xe).</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>ANPR</b></td>
      <td>Automatic Number Plate Recognition (Simulated gate camera scanning license plates).</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>EV</b></td>
      <td>Electric Vehicle.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>e-Ticket</b></td>
      <td>Electronic Parking Ticket displayed as a QR Code.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>PostgreSQL</b></td>
      <td>Relational Database Management System storing users, floors, slots, and vehicle logs.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Capacitor</b></td>
      <td>Hybrid app runtime tool converting Web code into a native Android package.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>1.4 References</h2>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>
- PostgreSQL Database Connection: <code>postgresql://postgres:12345@localhost:5432/nexus_parking</code><br>
- Express API server port: 8080<br>
- API Tunneling URL: <code>https://quouis.serveousercontent.com</code> (managed via live Serveo tunnel)<br>
- UI Theme Specs: Cyberpunk Dark Mode style guidelines.
</p>

<h2>1.5 Overview</h2>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>This document is organized into five main sections. Chapter 1 introduces the system. Chapter 2 outlines the client-server architecture and role permissions. Chapter 3 specifies the core use cases and flows. Chapter 4 documents the non-functional criteria. Chapter 5 details supporting information, including the relational database schemas and rates configuration.</p>

<div style='page-break-before:always;'></div>


<!-- ========================================== -->
<!-- 6. CONTENT SECTION 2 -->
<!-- ========================================== -->
<h1>2 OVERALL DESCRIPTION</h1>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>The NEXUS PBMS is built as a Client-Server application, with all data transactions consolidated in a PostgreSQL database. Changes to parking slot configurations, rates, and occupancy are synced dynamically to the client Web Dashboard and Android App via regular 2-second HTTP polling loops.</p>

<h3>User Roles & Access Permissions:</h3>
<ul type=disc>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Administrator (Admin)</b>: Full system administrator. Has access to all dashboard functions, settings, and analytics. Admins can view user directories (separated into Staff and Driver lists) and promote/demote user roles at any time.</li>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Staff</b>: Operational staff. Can access the core visual floor maps and the <b>Sender Management</b> tab to monitor parkings, review logs, and search for vehicles. Staff cannot access Settings or Analytics, and in the user table, they can only see Driver accounts (Admin and other Staff details are hidden).</li>
  <li style='margin-bottom:6.0pt;text-align:justify;'><b>Driver (User)</b>: Customer who registers and logs in on the Android mobile app to check in, receive assigned slots, monitor live parking fees, and checkout using QR codes.</li>
</ul>

<div style='page-break-before:always;'></div>


<!-- ========================================== -->
<!-- 7. CONTENT SECTION 3 -->
<!-- ========================================== -->
<h1>3 FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS</h1>

<h2>3.1 Use Cases Diagram</h2>
<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;'>Below is the textual representation of the core Use Case relationships:</p>
<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style='border-collapse:collapse;border:solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt;'>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th width="30%">Actor</th>
      <th>Permitted Use Cases</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Driver (Mobile App)</b></td>
      <td>Register, Login, Request Spot Allocation (Check-in), Track Live Bill, Display e-Ticket QR Code.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Staff (Operator Web)</b></td>
      <td>Login, Monitor Floor Grid Maps, View Sender Management List, Search Driver/Vehicle, View Security Logs.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><b>Admin (Full Web Dashboard)</b></td>
      <td>All Staff privileges, plus: Edit Rates, Manage User Roles (Promote/Demote), View Revenue Analytics Charts.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>3.2 Use Case Specifications</h2>

<h3>UC01: Automated Spot Allocation (Check-in)</h3>
<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style='border-collapse:collapse;border:solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt;margin-bottom:15.0pt;'>
  <tr>
    <td width="25%" style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Use-case No.</td>
    <td width="25%">&lt;UC01&gt;</td>
    <td width="25%" style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Use-case Version</td>
    <td width="25%">&lt;1.0&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Use-case Name</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;Automated Spot Allocation (Check-in)&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Author</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;NEXUS Dev Team&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Date</td>
    <td>24/06/2026</td>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Priority</td>
    <td>&lt;High&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Actors</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;Driver (Mobile App), Operator (Admin/Staff Web UI)&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Summary</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;A driver requests parking. The system checks the license plate, scans for a vacant parking slot matching the vehicle category, updates the slot state, and opens the entry gate barrier.&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Goal</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;To fully automate the check-in process, allocating parking spots efficiently without manual operator overhead.&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Triggers</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;Driver submits check-in form on the Mobile App, or ANPR camera detects plate at Gate A.&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Preconditions</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;At least one parking spot is vacant and available in the building.&gt;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style='background:#F2F2F2;font-weight:bold;'>Postconditions</td>
    <td colspan=3>&lt;The allocated slot status is set to "occupied", vehicle details are linked to the driver's username, and the e-Ticket is generated.&gt;</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p><b>Main Success Scenario:</b></p>
<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style='border-collapse:collapse;border:solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt;margin-bottom:10.0pt;'>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th width="10%">Step</th>
      <th width="45%">Actor Actions</th>
      <th width="45%">System Response</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td align=center>1</td>
      <td>Driver inputs license plate (e.g. 30A-123.45) and selects vehicle type (Car, SUV, EV, Motorbike, Handicap).</td>
      <td>System validates plate input format and performs duplicate plate verification.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td align=center>2</td>
      <td>Driver submits the check-in request.</td>
      <td>System searches database for a vacant spot in the preferred zone. If full, it searches the standard Car zone, and then falls back to any available spot.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td align=center>3</td>
      <td>Driver views the allocated slot details.</td>
      <td>System updates slot status to "occupied", sets check-in timestamp, links driver's username, and increments occupied slots.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td align=center>4</td>
      <td>Driver moves vehicle into the parking building.</td>
      <td>System opens the entry barrier for 3 seconds and generates the e-Ticket QR Code with a mini-navigation map.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p><b>Alternative Scenario:</b><br>
If the selected category zone is fully occupied, the system search falls back to standard Car slots. If those are also occupied, it allocates any random vacant slot in the entire parking garage.</p>

<p><b>Exceptions:</b><br>
<b>Duplicate Plate Error</b>: If the plate is already parked, system rejects entry and displays a red warning: <i>"Lỗi: Xe mang biển số [Plate] đã tồn tại trong bãi (vị trí [Slot ID])"</i>.</p>

<p><b>Business Rules:</b><br>
EV charging and charging surcharge are automatically activated if an EV vehicle is parked in an EV spot equipped with a charging station.</p>

<div style='page-break-before:always;'></div>

<h3>UC02: Visual Check-out & Payment</h3>
<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%" style='border-collapse:collapse;border:solid #BFBFBF 1.0pt;margin-bottom:15.0pt;'>
  <tr>
